			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Yes Sith, I do understand why people feel cheated.  But I do not think we have been.<BR>
<BR>
There are bugs with EQ, yes.  But there have always been bugs.  Frankly I don't expect EQ to ever be &quot;complete.&quot;  Thats the whole idea.  They are constantly adding things, changing things, removing things, fixing things.  If they ever reached a point where they said &quot;Thats it.  Everything is done.  Lets never change it again,&quot; the game would quickly dry up.<BR>
<BR>
There is certainly a complaint to make about certain features of SoL not working yet (bazzar, user interface, etc).  But these are issues for the Legends server as well....  You're assuming that there is no overlap between the two.<BR>
<BR>
My main point sipmly is;  I feel that the game has been fixed/adjusted at a reasonable rate since SoL came out.  Tech support has been a little slow, but that is to be expected after such a massive release.  Until the rate at which content and new features are added diminishes, I think we have nothing to complain about.
				</font>
