	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				One more thing<BR>
Quote:<BR>
--------------------------------------------<BR>
As far as revenue and the two developement teams being separate, that may be true. But we should still feel cheated. It is like Ranick said, Verant is making no income off these servers. The people paying $10 buck a month right now are paying the cost of developing and implimenting this separate game, while the version that they are paying for is still filled with bug related issues.<BR>
----------------------------------------------<BR>
<BR>
Quote: Mike<BR>
<BR>
That&#8217;s not necessarily true. When most companies add a service like this, they are able to develop and implement it without hurting the performance of their regular service. What they do is, they dip into their profit margins. Often they even go into dept, temporarily, with the hope that they will make up the difference later.<BR>
<BR>
Take your cable company for example. Most cable companies now offer digital cable for a higher cost. But did your regular cable service suffer while they were developing this technology? Mine certainly did not.<BR>
<BR>
Answer:<BR>
<BR>
Well, Mike, you kind of made my point for me.  Those profit margins you talk about dipping into, were created from the revenue earned off of customers paying $10 bucks a month.  Instead of tapping the profit to fix the game we pay for, they build a new version for Uber addicts with too much time and too much money.<BR>
<BR>
Also, our service is suffering.  The game is filled with bugs that should be addressed.  Instead they are diverting resourses to this new game and server.<BR>
<BR>
This is plain old bad buisness.  At this time Verant produces one product.  The customers deserve the best product Verant can provide.  Yet Verant is producing a separate product for a separate group of customers, all while the current product suffers.  Bad business plan.<BR>
<BR>
Here is another example from a different angle.  Company ABC make a Network System.  The only customer is has is Mega Corp.  The Network for Mega Corp isn't working properly and hasn't been working properly for sometime.  Company ABC has been working on the Network for Mega Corp, and adding upgrades and fixes here and there, but there are still major problems.<BR>
<BR>
Then one day, Company ABC says to Mega Corp.  We have a new Network to offer you.  We are also going to sell this Network to other companies.  It is a much better Network with more features and more services.  We built this new Network using the profits we made off you.  If you want to buy this new network it will cost you 4X the price of your current network.  Thank you, have a nice day.<BR>
<BR>
Do you think Mega Corp would be a bit mad that ABC Company was diverting resourses to an external product, external and hightly improved customer service all while the Network they were paying for was filled with problems?  I think they would.  Company ABC would not be a client of Mega Corp for very long if thats the way they did business.<BR>
<BR>
Mike, are you understanding why people are upset?  Do you see why this approach to product and customer service is a poor one on Verants part?  Would you as an owner of a company treat your clients like Verant is treating it's clients?<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
