			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				&gt;&gt;&gt; Second, you are misjudging the number of people it does take to keep EQ up and running. You have the 1200 computers that need to be kept up and running. You have to deal with maintaining them as servers as well. You have the local servers that people get routed through. And the CS department is MUCH larger than just 20 GM's. Think about how many people send in emails with technical problems each day. I know its been slow since Luclin, but i've always gotten a response within 48 hours. Thats a big undertaking. &lt;&lt;&lt; &lt;p&gt;<BR>
Ok let's think about this logically.  $10 a month times 400,000 subscribers equals $4,000,000 a month.  I work in the IT business and I can tell you that I can replace those 1200 server a few times over every month for that much money and still have enough left over to start a new company!  We are talking about $44,000,000 a year in subscriptions alone!  Plus they sell the software.  Was your copy of Shadows of Luclin free?  No.  Don't fool yourself because these people are making a killing on this game.  To sit there and tell me that $10 a month for the regular version of EQ is not bad really ticks me off.  Since when did the ONLY version of EQ become the REGULAR version.  As far as I knew, there was only ONE version until they decided to come out with this Legends thing.  I am more angry with the fact that the program we are devoted to is now going to be second rate when it comes to the EverQuest series.  We made Verant rich and now we are getting screwed as our thanks.  This is nothing short of exactly what Ford did by getting rich off of selling inexpensive cars and then over the years jacking the price up so that now the average consumer cant afford a Ford... unless you want the REGULAR version... aka the one that you have to use butter to squeeze yourself in to.  I just hope that when Verant finally gets tired of this REGULAR version of EQ they will sell it to a company that will actually give a d@mn about the people that support them.  Hell, I'll do it... send me $10 a month and I will put up 1200 servers for you!
